      "message": "[Critical] Line 1889: 🔴 Critical Issues - The recovery loop skips cloning when the only persisted member is the local account. That is a common case after a 1:1 conversation was accepted but member metadata was not fully populated or was partially stale. The corrupted conversation is left unloaded, no clone is scheduled, and the user permanently loses access until another startup path repairs metadata. Track whether at least one remote clone source was scheduled and either fall back to the conversation request/contact metadata or keep the conversation in a recoverable pending state with an explicit retry source. Example:\n```suggestion\nbool scheduled \u003d false;\nfor (const auto\u0026 member : shared-\u003egetConversationMembers(convId)) {\n    auto uriIt \u003d member.find(\"uri\");\n    if (uriIt \u003d\u003d member.end() || uriIt-\u003esecond.empty() || uriIt-\u003esecond \u003d\u003d shared-\u003eusername_)\n        continue;\n    scheduled \u003d true;\n    shared-\u003ecloneConversationFrom(convId, uriIt-\u003esecond);\n}\nif (!scheduled)\n    JAMI_WARNING(\"[Account {}] [Conversation {}] No remote member available for repository recovery\", shared-\u003eaccountId_, convId);\n```",
