      "message": "[Critical] Line 3900: 🔴 Critical Issues - `validate()` checks blob/subtree presence with `git_odb_exists()`, which can succeed from the pack index even when the pack data is truncated or unreadable. The new API documentation explicitly claims it detects truncated packs, but this implementation may still mark such repositories valid and re-enter the fetch/merge failure loop later when content is inflated. Read object headers for every reachable object instead of only checking index presence, while still avoiding blob payload inflation. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nsize_t len \u003d 0;\ngit_object_t type \u003d GIT_OBJECT_ANY;\nif (git_odb_read_header(\u0026len, \u0026type, ctx-\u003eodb, id) \u003c 0)\n    return -1;\n```",
