      "message": "[Medium] Line 57: 🟡 Suggestions - `makeGitObjectUnreachable()` returns true even if `std::filesystem::remove()` fails, because the error code is ignored. That can make corruption tests pass the setup assertion while the object still exists, leaving the test to fail later with a misleading `validate()` assertion. Check the remove result and error code explicitly.\n```suggestion\nif (std::filesystem::exists(loose, ec)) {\n    ec.clear();\n    return std::filesystem::remove(loose, ec) \u0026\u0026 !ec;\n}\n```",
